'''Solarized''' is a [[color scheme]] designed by Ethan Schoonover.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ethanschoonover.com/solarized |title=Solarized |first=Ethan|last= Schoonover |accessdate=February 10, 2017}}</ref> It comes in two variants known as '''Solarized Light''' and '''Solarized Dark'''. The color scheme can be used by [[text editor]]s and [[integrated development environment]]s for [[syntax highlighting]].<ref name="observer">{{cite web |url=http://observer.com/2015/02/meet-the-man-behind-solarized-the-most-important-color-scheme-in-computer-history/ |title=Meet the Man Behind 'Solarized,' the Most Important Color Scheme in Computer History |date=February 27, 2015 |publisher=Observer |accessdate=February 10, 2017 |author=Jack Smith IV}}</ref>

<ref>{{cite web |url=https://usesthis.com/interviews/ethan.schoonover/ |author=Daniel Bogan |title=The Setup / Ethan Schoonover |accessdate=February 10, 2017}}</ref>

==History==

Schoonover began designing Solarized in 2010. The process of choosing the colors took "six months of research and tweaking".<ref name="observer" />

Schoonover announced in April 2011 that he is "hard at work on beta2".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metafilter.com/102504/Solarized#3636286 |title=Solarized |publisher=[[MetaFilter]] |accessdate=February 10, 2017}}</ref>

<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ethanschoonover.com/solarized/CHANGELOG |author= |title=CHANGELOG - Ethan Schoonover |accessdate=February 10, 2017}}</ref>

==Features==

The same palette works for both the light and dark variants.

==Availability==

Solarized [[configuration file]]s exist for the following programs, or Solarized is otherwise available for these programs:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/solarized |title=Solarized - Precision colors for machines and people |accessdate=February 10, 2017}}</ref>

{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}
* [[X resources]] (for [[xterm]], [[rxvt-unicode]], etc.)
* Terminal emulators ([[Terminal (Xfce)|Xfce Terminal]])
* gedit
* [[tmux]]
* [[XChat]]
* [[Qt Creator]]
* [[Mutt (email client)|Mutt]]
* [[Vim (text editor)|Vim]]
* [[Emacs]]
* [[iTerm2]]
* [[Terminal (macOS)|Terminal.app]]
* [[Sublime Text]]
* [[GNOME Terminal]]
* [[Terminator (terminal emulator)|Terminator]]
* [[BBEdit]]/[[TextWrangler]]
* [[Visual Studio]]
* [[TextMate]]
* st (the terminal emulator developed at [[suckless.org]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://st.suckless.org/patches/solarized |title=solarized {{!}} suckless.org st - simple terminal |accessdate=February 10, 2017}}</ref>
* [[MATLAB]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://github.com/Chrismarsh/matlab-solarized |title=The Solarized theme for Matlab}}</ref>
{{Div col end}}

As [[color palette]]s, Solarized is also available on [[Adobe Photoshop]], [[Apple Color Picker]], and [[GIMP]].

However, as Solarized is a color scheme, it is possible to port it to any program that supports custom color schemes.

